description: Bengal witnessed brisker polling pace till 5pm on Saturday in the penultimate phase, marred by the murder of a Trinamool Congress worker in East Midnapore's Mahisadal and near fatal attack on another. Poll-day demonstrations against BJP candidates occurred in Keshpur and Egra.

description: PM Modi criticized Congress and RJD for corruption and a 'Muslim appeasement policy', vowed to fight for OBCs, SCs, and STs quota, and warned against 'jungle raj' in Bihar during election rallies.

description: Exposure to air pollutants, including PM2.5, may increase the risk of Type 2 diabetes. Recent studies, like one from JAPI, link PM2.5 to elevated blood sugar levels, highlighting air pollution's health impacts.

description: A senior doctor from BMC, Dr. Rajesh Dere, arrested for causing the death of Rubaida Shaikh in a car accident at Sion hospital. The incident involved negligence and rash driving.

description: One person died and six were injured in a massive blast at an explosives factory in Bemetara district, Chhattisgarh. Rescuers suspect more victims are buried in the rubble.

description: Severe Cyclone Remal is set to strike the Bengal-Bangladesh coast with wind speeds of 70-80kmph, gusting up to 90kmph, leading to very heavy rainfall. Netaji Subhas Chandra Bose International Airport will shut down for 21 hours, resulting in the cancellation of 394 flights affecting 63,000 passengers.

description: Three Maoists were killed in encounters in Sukma and Bijapur districts of Bastar division, Chhattisgarh. The Maoist body count this year has reached 116, with 11 deaths in the last three days.

description: Around 61.2 per cent of the electorate turned up to vote in the sixth and penultimate round of polling Saturday - marking completion of polling in 90 per cent of Lok Sabha seats. Only one phase remains now, for 57 seats on June 1, before counting on June 4.

description: A 30-year-old man, posing as a woman teacher using a voice-changing app, sexually assaulted seven tribal girls in MP's Sidhi district. CM Mohan Yadav ordered a nine-member SIT to investigate the case of serial rape related to SC/ST scholarships.

description: ​Intense heat, extended weekend, and general indifference seem to have caused a drop of close to 4.5 percentage points in voter turnout in the capital for the parliamentary elections on Saturday. The city was electing seven members of the Lok Sabha after intense campaigning by BJP, AAP, and Congress, the latter two having struck an alliance.

description: Uttarakhand's Uniform Civil Code, led by former chief secretary Shatrughan Singh, plans online registration for live-ins. Training for govt employees, including sub-registrar office staff, is crucial.

description: Dance Deewane Season 4 concluded with Gaurav Sharma and Nithin NJ emerging as winners. Judged by Madhuri Dixit Nene and Suniel Shetty, the show featured unique communication challenges overcome through dance.
title: Dance Deewane 4 winners Gaurav Sharma and Nithin NJ

description: The election process in Assam, which was conducted in three phases, has come to an end. Voters in the state have cast their ballots for 14 parliamentary seats and are now eagerly anticipating the outcome, which will be announced on June 4. This marks the first Lok Sabha elections held in Assam since the controversial Citizenship Amendment Act (CAA) came into effect.

description: The first batch of Indian players including skipper Rohit Sharma, pace spearhead Jasprit Bumrah and number one ranked T20I batter Suryakumar Yadav left for the United States ahead of the ICC T20 World Cup starting from June 1 onwards.

description: Tracy Hickman, a 37-year-old British woman with terminal breast cancer, peacefully passed away through euthanasia on a beach in New Zealand, surrounded by loved ones. She advocated for assisted dying rights and hoped for better UK legislation. Linda Clarke supported her decision. The 'End of Life Choice Act' permits euthanasia for adults with terminal illnesses.

description: As a leader, Pat Cummins has achieved remarkable success at the pinnacle of the sport. He is now on the verge of adding another significant accomplishment to his already impressive resume by securing the IPL title.

description: Amid speculation that Rahul Dravid may not continue as head coach post the T20 World Cup in the Americas, several Australians, such as Ricky Ponting and Justin Langer, have been linked to the position. However, each has expressed their reluctance to take on the role, citing personal reasons. Meanwhile, the BCCI has denied approaching any former Australian cricketer for the prestigious position, despite the rumors circulating in the media.

description: PM Modi thanked voters in the penultimate phase of the Lok Sabha election, stating NDA's strong numbers. West Bengal saw the highest voter turnout amid some violence incidents.

description: As Phase 6 of Lok Sabha elections concluded on Saturday, the overall voter turnout was recorded at 59.46 per cent. In Phase 6, 58 seats went to polling across eight states and UTs. This is the lowest turnout till now among all six phases of Lok Sabha. The highest turnout of 78.14 per cent was recorded in West Bengal.

description: A sudden downpour disrupted Kolkata Knight Riders' final practice session before their crucial IPL final showdown against Sunrisers Hyderabad on Sunday. While SRH enjoyed a day off, KKR were slated for an evening practice under floodlights. However, just as the players began their customary warm-up football game, rain poured down, forcing them indoors. Despite the scramble for shelter, ground staff managed to cover the fourth strip designated for the final match.

The leaders expressed their disapproval of the Prime Minister's use of the term "mujra" to refer to the INDIA bloc.

He said that Agniveers will receive a hefty salary for 4 years and after that will get a permanent job with gratuity. Shah criticised Gandhi for misguiding the public about the scheme.

description: Apple has faced an unexpected challenge in India with cash payments, leading to the installation of currency note counting machines in Mumbai and Delhi stores. Sales in these stores show 7-9% cash transactions, much higher than in the US or Europe.

description: Sharing pictures of EVMs which had paper tags with BJP written on them, the TMC said on X, "Smt. @MamataOfficial has repeatedly flagged how @BJP4India was trying to rig votes by tampering with EVMs. And today, in Bankura's Raghunathpur, 5 EVMs were found with BJP tags on them." The poll body, however, promptly replied to the claim and justified the tags. "While commissioning, common address tags were signed by the Candidates and their agents present. And since only BJP Candidate's representative was present during that time in the commissioning hall, his signature was taken during commissioning of that EVM and VVPAT," the poll body replied on the social media platform.

The disaster occurred in Kaokalam village, Enga Province, at around 3 am on Friday, about 600 km northwest of the capital, Port Moresby. According to the Papua New Guinea Post Courier, Member of Parliament Aimos Akem confirmed that 1,182 houses were buried in the landslide.

title: Man posing as female teacher using voice changing app raped 7 girls

description: The Pune police arrested a grandfather and father after they forced their driver to falsely confess to an accident caused by a juvenile family member. The driver was confined in their bungalow from May 19 to May 20 before his wife freed him. They face charges under IPC sections 365 and 368 for kidnapping and wrongful confinement.

Sharma's precise swinging deliveries, capturing the wickets of Travis Head and Heinrich Klaasen, were impressive. Samson praised Sharma as the "next guy" after India's premier fast bowler, Jasprit Bumrah.

The Royals were outplayed at Chepauk, losing crucial wickets to spinners Shahbaz Ahmed and Abhishek Sharma. Cummins' shift to spin on the spinning Chepauk pitch led to five wickets for SRH.

description: Documentary filmmaker Morgan Spurlock, known for 'Super Size Me,' passes away at 53. His impactful work tackled societal issues, from fast food's impact on health to product placement. Despite acclaim, Spurlock faced controversy over sexual misconduct allegations. Survived by two sons, parents, and siblings, Spurlock's legacy extends beyond filmmaking, inspiring activism. His contributions to social justice and filmmaking will be remembered globally.

description: SBI warns customers about fraudulent messages and APKs, clarifies not sending unsolicited links over SMS or WhatsApp.
title: SBI has important warning on these SMS and WhatsApp messages

description: Delhi is voting on May 25 in the sixth phase of elections to elect seven candidates to the Lok Sabha. The BJP, which secured all seven seats in both the 2014 and 2019 elections, is confident of another victory. This time, its rivals, Delhi chief minister Arvind Kejriwal's AAP and the Congress, have formed an alliance to break the BJP's winning streak, having contested separately in previous polls. So, price reduction for Range Rover Autobiography model will be Rs 60 lakh and it will now come for Rs 2.6 crore (ex-showroom).
